# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  RESUMINT AI — Frontend environment variables (.env)
#  Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the PUBLISHABLE values only.
#
#  ⚠️  NEVER put secret keys here. A Vite app is fully client-side, so
#      anything in this file ships in the browser bundle and is public.
#      Secrets (OpenAI, Resend, DB password, NextAuth secret) live ONLY
#      on your server / Supabase Edge Function.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Point at a custom backend (optional). If set, auth/ai calls go here.
# VITE_API_BASE=https://your-backend.example.com

# OR: set your Supabase project URL (publishable). When set WITHOUT a custom
# backend, the OTP flow auto-targets your deployed Edge Function:
#   <VITE_SUPABASE_URL>/functions/v1/send-otp
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co

# Supabase ANON key is publishable-safe (that's why Next.js uses NEXT_PUBLIC_).
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ── Secrets that must ONLY exist server-side (Supabase → Project Settings →
#    Edge Function Secrets). Do NOT reference them anywhere in this repo:
#    RESEND_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, NEXTAUTH_SECRET, DATABASE_URL
